Package: winn
Title: White Noise Normalization for Metabolomics LC-MS Data
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: person(given = "Tanmay", family = "Tanna", email = "ttanna@ethz.ch", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Tanmay Tanna [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Tanmay Tanna <ttanna@ethz.ch>
Description: Provides a decision-guided workflow for correcting technical
    variability in metabolomics data while preserving metabolites that already
    satisfy a white-noise gatekeeper. The package combines robust outlier
    adjustment, adaptive drift detection, fkPELT-based batch segmentation,
    batch correction, and probabilistic quotient normalization in a single
    pipeline or as modular steps. It supports QC-informed parameter tuning as
    well as QC-agnostic operation for studies without pooled controls. The
    underlying white-noise normalization strategy is aligned with the WiNN
    framework described in Demler et al. (2020) <doi:10.7490/f1000research.1118070.1>.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
